HEADWORD: magnetic needle
<hw>magnetic needle</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A slender magnet suspended
in a magnetic compass on a low-friction mounting; used to indicate the
direction of the earth's magnetic pole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>magnetic north</ent>⟦br⟧
